      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ARTICOLE (3) won in a photo finish at Northam last start after sitting wide in the run. A better draw this time suits him much better and Fiore remains in the irons. Looks a nice gelding on the way up and with that run under his belt, he can land the knockout blow once again. LIGHT OF THE WORLD (8) jumped favourite last start and led them up at Northam, being caught right on the post to miss in a photo finish. He's a 2YO taking on the older horses and back to 1200m now looks a good move. Draws well again and can notch up his maiden win. FRIAR'S LEGACY (1) is racing well without winning this time in and maps to sit much closer this time around. ZJP's claim comes in handy and she can sit close to the speed. Sure to be there at the finish. RADIANT LIGHT (6) can give them something to chase after a good win last time out. SUPIDO EXPRESS (2) is third-up now and can put his best foot forward.",
